This restaurant is nothing to write home about.  There isn’t even a full bar.  To begin with, our waiter asked us if we had any allergies he should be aware of. We both said yes and told him that I have a gluten allergy. It’s like he was program to ask but had no clue what had gluten in it and what didn’t. We share food, so we wanted everything to be gluten-free even though my husband can eat gluten. He is sweet and accommodates me. There were a handful of items that were not specifically marked gluten-free but looks like they could be safe. We had specifically inquired about those items and the waiter assured us that they were OK. The items arrived, and what do you know? They had gluten in them! One of them had a sauce that contained regular soy sauce, which contains gluten, over top it. The yellowtail roll had fake crab in it. The fake crab has gluten in it because it’s Connie fish and how they get it to stick together in the texture that resembles crab is with a binder that contains gluten. This guy had no clue! Thank God we are super safe and ask before hand. The sangrias were OK but they were anything that I’d go in there for. The cod was marked gluten-free so we got it. It did not taste good at all. I would highly recommend to steer clear of that.  Beyond that, in the span of 20 minutes, for dishes were broken. It was unreal and sounded like a fight. It wasn’t a good and inviting atmosphere.  Again, I would not recommend this place at all!
